steps.description:
Edit the Claude Desktop config to register kubestellar-mcp as an MCP server. Replace `<path>` with the absolute path to the binary (find with `which kubestellar-mcp`):
```json
{
  "mcpServers": {
    "kubestellar": {
      "command": "/opt/homebrew/bin/kubestellar-mcp",
      "args": [],
      "env": {
        "KUBECONFIG": "/Users/<you>/.kube/config"
      }
    }
  }
}
```
Claude Desktop re-reads the config on restart, so quit the app completely (`Cmd+Q` on macOS) and relaunch it. On next launch, the MCP tool icon should appear in the chat composer — click it to see the kubestellar tools the server exposes.
